  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "At a special executive session to-\nnight of the 100000 club, officers\nof the organization will discuss the\nright Of way desired over the Fort\nWright military reservation by the\nPortland & Seattle railroad. E. j.\nCannon, division counsel, at meet\ning with the club officers and other\ninterested parties last week, threat\nened to build a 40 foot dixie across\nthe city if the company was inter-\nferred with in its plans to build in\nfront of the fort buildings. The\n$50, 900 club wants the route to go\nbehind the buildings. At the exc\ncutive session tonight a date will\nbe decided on for a public mass\nmeeting."
    }
  ]
